## Problem 5: Linear Classifier / SVM Decision Function

A classifier has:

$$
w=\begin{bmatrix}2 \ -1\end{bmatrix}, \quad b=1
$$

For input

$$
x=\begin{bmatrix}3 \ 4\end{bmatrix}
$$

compute

$$
f(x)=w^T x+b
$$

and determine the predicted class using sign.

### Solution

First compute dot product:

$$
w^T x=(2)(3)+(-1)(4)=6-4=2
$$

Now add bias:

$$
f(x)=2+1=3
$$

Prediction:

$$
\hat y=\text{sign}(3)=+1
$$

**Answer: (f(x)=3), predicted class = positive**

